That the following article is proposed as an amendment to the 
Constitution of the United States, which shall be valid to all intents and 
purposes as part of the Constitution when ratified by the legislatures of 
three-fourths of the several States: 
"Article ___
Section 1:
The Vice President shall be elected by national popular vote in 
accordance with this Constitution, by a ballot option separate from any 
other office.
Section 2:
Before taking office, the Vice President Elect will take the following 
Oath or Affirmation: “I do solemnly swear (or affirm) that I will 
faithfully execute the Office of Vice President of the United States, and 
will to the best of my Ability, preserve, protect and defend the
Constitution of the United States.” ”
